doc.after: The New Jersey Turnpike is one of the most prominent and heavily traveled roadways in the United States This toll road carries interstate traffic between Delaware and New York and the East Coast in general Commonly referred to as simply the Turnpike it is known for its numerous rest areas named after prominent New Jerseyans as diverse as inventor Thomas Edison United States Secretary of the Treasury Alexander Hamilton United States Presidents Grover Cleveland and Woodrow Wilson writers James Fenimore Cooper Joyce Kilmer and Walt Whitman patriot Molly Pitcher Red Cross founder Clara Barton and football coach Vince Lombardi
